main event: A circular, clear but bright object was observed over Louisville, Kentucky for 3 to 5 minutes on November 26, 1957.
interesting points: The object was circular and appeared to be one-half inch in diameter.
The object was in sight for 3 to 5 minutes.
The description, duration, flight path, and altitude indicate that the object was possibly a balloon.
A previous sighting of a white object with a red stripe was observed in the same area for 45 minutes over the course of a week.
The previous sighting was concluded to be likely the planet Venus.
